European Stocks Gain, U.S. Futures Are Little Changed; Credit Suisse Rises

-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 
2011-02-14T08:06:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/european-stocks-gain-u-s-futures-are-little-changed-credit-suisse-rises.html
European stocks rose, extending the
Stoxx Europe 600 Index’s two-week rally, as the Japanese economy
shrank less than forecast. U.S. futures were little changed and
Asian shares advanced.  Credit Suisse Group AG climbed 2.2 percent after saying it
will sell notes to investors Qatar Holding LLC and The Olayan
Group. Nexans SA jumped 2.7 percent after the world’s largest
cable maker reported an increase in profit. Cable & Wireless
Communications Plc lost 2 percent as UBS AG advised selling the
shares.  The benchmark Stoxx 600 added 0.6 percent to 289.66 at 8:04
a.m. in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Hadfield at 
 whadfield@bloomberg.net  